<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-631-751  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 631 751.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Nov 19 1990 n493 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hughes crosses into EDS turf. (Hughes Aircraft Co establishes asystems integration subsidiary that may compete with ElectronicData Systems Corp)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Alper, Alan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hughes Aircraft Co establishes a systems integration subsidiarythat may compete with Electronic Data Systems Corp (EDS) forfederal and commercial contracts; both Hughes and EDS are owned byGeneral Motors Corp. Hughes has hired former Planning ResearchCorp Chmn Wayne Shelton to head the new firm, to be called HughesInformation Technology Co; the new company will target large-scalefederal government projects at first and will coordinate many ofthe systems integration activities of other Hughes units.andO;Executives will be recruited for Hughes Information Technologyfrom among other Hughes space, radar systems and communicationsoperations, and companies with complementary informationtechnology skills may be acquired.andP;  Sources indicated that the newcompany will move slowly toward commercial integration projects,applying its expertise in defense systems and air traffic controlto civilian projects.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hughes Information Technology Co. (Marketing)Hughes Aircraft Co. (Management).andO;Ticker:    GM.andO;Topic:     Computer Systems IntegratorsNew CompaniesSubsidiary CompaniesMarketing StrategyCompetitionOrganization Structure.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Wayne Shelton. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>